# {{ project_name }} - Authentication Provider Migration Guide

This guide helps you migrate between authentication providers (Auth.js, Clerk, and Better Auth) in your SaaS application. Each provider has different strengths, and you may need to switch based on evolving requirements.

---

## When to Migrate Authentication Providers

**Migrate FROM Clerk TO Auth.js if:**
- You need full control over authentication logic
- You want to reduce monthly costs (Auth.js is self-hosted and free)
- You prefer managing your own infrastructure
- You need custom authentication flows not supported by Clerk
- You want to avoid vendor lock-in

**Migrate FROM Auth.js TO Clerk if:**
- You want to reduce engineering overhead
- You need enterprise features (SSO, SAML, organizations)
- You prefer a managed solution with high uptime SLA
- You need built-in UI components and pre-built components
- You want organization-first multi-tenancy out-of-the-box

**Migrate TO Better Auth if:**
- You want a lightweight, modern alternative to Auth.js
- You prefer TypeScript-first authentication
- You need flexible, customizable backends
- You want better edge-runtime compatibility

---

## Provider Comparison Table

| Feature | Auth.js | Clerk | Better Auth |
|---------|---------|-------|------------|
| **Cost** | Free (self-hosted) | $25-100+/mo | Free (self-hosted) |
| **Setup Complexity** | Medium | Low | Medium |
| **Multi-Tenancy** | Custom implementation | Built-in Organizations | Custom implementation |
| **OAuth Providers** | 15+ | 10+ | 10+ |
| **Passwordless** | No | Yes (passkeys) | Yes |
| **SSO/SAML** | No | Yes (Enterprise) | No |
| **UI Components** | None | React components | None |
| **Session Storage** | Database or JWT | JWT (hosted) | Database or JWT |
| **Self-Hosted** | Yes | No | Yes |
| **Database Adapters** | Prisma, Drizzle | Only internal | Prisma, Drizzle |
| **Edge Runtime Support** | Partial | Yes | Yes |
| **Learning Curve** | Steep | Shallow | Medium |
| **Community Size** | Large | Large | Growing |

