## Part 3: Auth.js → Better Auth Migration

### Step 1: Install Better Auth

```bash
# Remove Auth.js
pnpm remove next-auth @auth/prisma-adapter @auth/drizzle-adapter

# Add Better Auth
pnpm add better-auth
```

### Step 2: Set Up Better Auth

Create `/lib/auth/better-auth.config.ts`:

```typescript
import { betterAuth } from "better-auth";
{% if saas_orm == "prisma" %}
import { PrismaClient } from "@prisma/client";

const prisma = new PrismaClient();
{% elif saas_orm == "drizzle" %}
import { db } from "@/lib/database/client";
{% endif %}

export const auth = betterAuth({
  database: {% if saas_orm == "prisma" %}{
    db: prisma,
    type: "prisma",
  }{% elif saas_orm == "drizzle" %}{
    db: db,
    type: "drizzle",
  }{% endif %},

  secret: process.env.BETTER_AUTH_SECRET,

  emailAndPassword: {
    enabled: true,
  },

  socialProviders: {
    google: {
      clientId: process.env.GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID,
      clientSecret: process.env.GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET,
    },
    github: {
      clientId: process.env.GITHUB_CLIENT_ID,
      clientSecret: process.env.GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET,
    },
  },

  trustedOrigins: [process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL!],
});

export type Session = typeof auth.$Infer.Session;
```

### Step 3: Create API Routes

Create `/app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts`:

```typescript
import { auth } from "@/lib/auth/better-auth.config";

export const { POST, GET } = auth.toNextJsHandler();
```

### Step 4: Update Environment Variables

```bash
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=your-secret-here
BETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000

GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=...
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=...
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=...
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=...
```

### Step 5: Replace Components

Use `better-auth` client hooks:

```typescript
'use client';

import { useSession, signOut } from "@/lib/auth/client";

export function Dashboard() {
  const { data: session, isPending } = useSession();

  if (isPending) return <div>Loading...</div>;

  return (
    <div>
      <p>Hello {session?.user.name}</p>
      <button onClick={() => signOut()}>Sign Out</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

