## Testing Your Migration

### Pre-Migration Checklist

- [ ] Backup production database
- [ ] Export all user data
- [ ] Test migration scripts in staging environment
- [ ] Verify environment variables are set
- [ ] Ensure new provider infrastructure is ready

### Testing Auth Flows

```typescript
// tests/auth-migration.spec.ts
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('Can sign up with OAuth', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/sign-up');
  await page.click('button:has-text("Sign up with Google")');
  // OAuth provider login flow
  await page.waitForURL('/dashboard');
  expect(await page.locator('text=Dashboard').isVisible()).toBeTruthy();
});

test('Session persists after refresh', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/dashboard');
  // Should redirect to sign-in if not authenticated
  const url = page.url();
  expect(url).toContain('sign-in');
});

test('Protected API route requires auth', async ({ request }) => {
  const response = await request.get('/api/profile');
  expect(response.status()).toBe(401);
});

test('Signed in users can access protected routes', async ({ page }) => {
  // After signing in
  await page.goto('/dashboard');
  expect(page.url()).toContain('dashboard');
});
```

### Verification Steps

1. **Sign up flow** - Create new account
2. **OAuth providers** - Test Google and GitHub login
3. **Session persistence** - Refresh page and verify session survives
4. **Protected routes** - Verify redirect to sign-in when logged out
5. **API authentication** - Test protected endpoints
6. **User data** - Verify user information appears correctly
7. **Sign out flow** - Test logout and session clearing

